FBIS4-41109 "drsov120_b_94017" FBIS-SOV-94-120 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military, Nuclear & Space Issues Yeltsin Sets Up Commission on Senior Military Posts Yeltsin Sets Up Commission on Senior Military Posts LD2106162894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0859 GMT 21 Jun 94 LD2106162894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [By ITAR-TASS] [Text] Moscow, 21 Jun -- On Monday Boris Yeltsin approved the statute of a commission for higher military posts, higher military ranks, and higher special ranks of the council for cadre policy under the Russian president. The commission's task is to examine the representations by heads of federal bodies of executive authority of the Russian president on appointing servicemen to top military posts and on relieving them of these posts in the Defense Ministry, the Interior Ministry, bodies and troops of the federal agency of government communications and information, counterintelligence bodies, the main directorate for protection, the security service of the Russian president, the foreign intelligence service, and other formations.
